name: First Visit! Air Canada Rouge 767-333ER(WL) [C-GHLQ] Dusk Landing at Calgary Airport ᴴᴰ
description:
In their (almost) three years of operations, Air Canada Rouge has never sent one of their Boeing 767-300ER aircraft to Calgary International Airport. That changed today when C-GHLQ operated RV1863, Calgary's daily service to Las Vegas, as a rare equipment swap, arriving in the last few minutes of light on runway 17L. Not only is this a first for YYC, but it's a first for me as well. Prior to today, this was the only aircraft from Air Canada that I had never seen before. This bird sure looks good with those 11 foot tall winglets. ATC is included with captions as usual, enjoy!

Thanks for watching! Please comment, rate, and subscribe!
